    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="856"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d856">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Fava</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: With the most intense grief I
                    discharge the sad duty of announcing to your excellency that His Majesty King
                    Humbert died last night, the 29th instant, a victim of an infamous assault.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to beg your excellency to be pleased to impart this mournful
                    intelligence to the President of the United States.</p>
                <p>His Majesty King Victor Emanuel III is now at Piresus, whence he is about to
                    return to the Kingdom.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fava.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
